# Patch: telemetry-strip-tracking

Removes the telemetry tracking surface from `vendor/vercel-skills/telemetry.ts`.

## Rationale

ADR-002 §Vendoring: "Vendored modules MUST be: `telemetry.ts` (audit subset
only; strip telemetry tracking)". Hotskills wants the audit API client
(`fetchAuditData` + types) but does not want a tracking pixel embedded in
the MCP server binary.

## Removed symbols

- `TELEMETRY_URL` constant
- `track()` function
- `setVersion()` function
- `cliVersion` mutable module-level state
- `isCI()` function
- `isEnabled()` function
- Type aliases / interfaces: `InstallTelemetryData`, `RemoveTelemetryData`,
  `UpdateTelemetryData`, `FindTelemetryData`, `SyncTelemetryData`,
  `TelemetryData`

## Retained symbols

- `AUDIT_URL` constant
- `PartnerAudit` interface
- `SkillAuditData` type alias
- `AuditResponse` type alias
- `fetchAuditData()` function (verbatim)

## Conceptual diff

```diff
- const TELEMETRY_URL = 'https://add-skill.vercel.sh/t';
  const AUDIT_URL = 'https://add-skill.vercel.sh/audit';

- interface InstallTelemetryData { ... }
- interface RemoveTelemetryData { ... }
- interface UpdateTelemetryData { ... }
- interface FindTelemetryData { ... }
- interface SyncTelemetryData { ... }
- type TelemetryData = ... ;
-
- let cliVersion: string | null = null;
-
- function isCI(): boolean { ... }
- function isEnabled(): boolean { ... }
- export function setVersion(version: string): void { ... }

  // ─── Security audit data ───  (retained verbatim)
  export interface PartnerAudit { ... }
  export type SkillAuditData = ...;
  export type AuditResponse = ...;
  export async function fetchAuditData(...) { ... }

- export function track(data: TelemetryData): void { ... }
```

## Drift-check guidance

The vendor-drift CI workflow (`hotskills-35o`) MUST apply this patch in
reverse before diffing the upstream `src/telemetry.ts` against the
vendored copy. A simple approximation: strip everything between
`vendored-from-END` and the `// ─── Security audit data ───` divider in
the vendored file, then diff only the audit subset against the matching
section of upstream.
